 {"id":"asupersync-1f3ww","title":"Implement two-phase MPSC channel with reserve/commit","description":"## Purpose
Implement the cancel-safe MPSC (multi-producer, single-consumer) channel primitive using the two-phase reserve/commit pattern. This is a foundational primitive that prevents message loss during cancellation.

## The Problem with Traditional Channels
```rust
// Traditional tokio channel - NOT cancel-safe\!
tx.send(message).await?;  // If cancelled here, message may be lost\!
```

The send operation interleaves reservation and commitment. If cancelled between allocation and commit, the message vanishes.

## Two-Phase Solution
```rust
// Asupersync channel - cancel-safe\!
let permit = tx.reserve(cx).await?;  // Phase 1: reserve slot
permit.send(message);                 // Phase 2: commit (cannot fail)
```

### Phase 1: Reserve
- Allocates channel slot
- Creates obligation (SendPermit) in Created state
- Can be cancelled safely - nothing committed yet
- Returns permit handle

### Phase 2: Commit
- `permit.send(message)`: Commits message, resolves obligation
- `permit.abort()`: Releases slot, resolves obligation with Aborted
- `drop(permit)`: Equivalent to abort (RAII cleanup)

