## Capacity and Backpressure
- `mpsc::channel<T>(capacity)`: Creates bounded channel
- Reserve blocks when full (backpressure)
- Capacity is "slots reserved + messages in queue"

## Cancellation Scenarios
| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| Cancel during reserve wait | Clean abort, no message sent |
| Cancel after reserve, before send | Permit dropped, slot released |
| Cancel during recv wait | Clean abort |
| Sender dropped with pending permits | All permits abort on drop |
| Receiver dropped | All senders get SendError::Disconnected |

## Invariant Support
- **No silent drops**: Message only committed via `permit.send()`
- **Obligation tracking**: SendPermit and RecvPermit are obligations
- **Cancel-safety**: Cancellation at any point results in clean state

